<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
 <head>
  <title>CSS Test: Background of special elements</title>
  <link rel="author" title="Bert Bos" href="mailto:bert@w3.org" />
  <link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/css3-background/#special-backgrounds" />
  <meta name="flags" content="" />
  <meta name="assert" content="The background of the root element becomes the background of the canvas and its background painting area extends to cover the entire canvas." />
  <style type="text/css"><![CDATA[
   :root {background-image: none; background-color: green;
     margin: 2em; padding: 0}
   body {margin: 0}
   p {color: black; margin: 0}
  ]]></style>
 </head>
 <body>
  <p>Test passes if the background of the page (outside this paragraph) is green.</p>
  <!--[Content of test]-->
 </body>
</html>
